==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, from Indo-European ''*u̯eig-, *u̯eik-'' ‘bend, wind’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[wika]] (Dutch [[week#Dutch|week]]), Old High German [[wehha]] (German [[Woche]]), Old Norse [[vika]] (Swedish [[vecka]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌹𐌺𐍉]].

